history.content: There is no discussion section where the # of spaces is smaller than the existing waitlist so I'm not certain what motivated the attempt but it is true that all sections and the lecture have waitlists and space in those waitlists so I'm also confused as to what is blocking you from re-adding to the waitlist.

I was on the waitlist for CS70 this summer but there was an open discussion time, so I had to drop the class and re-add it with the open discussion, but now it won't let me add the class. I checked http://classes.berkeley.edu/content/2018-summer-compsci-70-001-lec-001 and there still seems to be open seats for the waitlist, so I'm not sure why it's saying this. Any help would be appreciated!
history.subject: Can't enroll in CS70 Summer
